SIMPLE: imaginal
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Imaginal
<hw>Im*ag"i*nal</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>imaginalis</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Characterized by
imagination; imaginative; also, given to the use or rhetorical figures
or imagines.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Of or pertaining to an
imago.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Imaginal disks</b></col> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>masses
of hypodermic cells, carried by the larv⟦ae⟧ of some insects after
leaving the egg, from which masses the wings and legs of the adult are
subsequently formed.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Imaginant</ent>⟦br⟧
